Package: kora-cuda
Version: __VERSION__
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: __ARCH__
Installed-Size: __INSTALLED_SIZE__
Maintainer: willgcr <hello@willgcr.me>
Depends: kora (>= __VERSION__), libc6
Recommends: nvidia-driver-libs | libnvidia-compute-550
Homepage: https://wrklabs.org/kora
Description: CUDA backend addon for kora
 Adds the CUDA backend plugin to kora's runtime backend directory, so
 kora's vendored llama.cpp uses CUDA on NVIDIA GPUs instead of Vulkan.
 .
 This is a thin addon — it ships only libggml-cuda.so plus the bundled
 CUDA runtime libraries (libcudart, libcublas, libcublasLt). All of
 kora's actual functionality lives in the kora package, which this
 package depends on; installing kora-cuda alone pulls kora in.
 .
 Requires an NVIDIA GPU and a working NVIDIA driver. To remove CUDA
 acceleration without uninstalling kora, simply remove this package —
 kora falls back to Vulkan or CPU automatically.
